The paper deals with a coloring problem on dynamic point sets, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of hypergraphs and the study of cover-decomposability suggest a connection to discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and graph theory (cs.GT). Finally, the algorithmic aspect of the problem and the lower bound analysis indicate a possible connection to computational complexity (cs.CC).
